# Process of creating the persistent volumes in k8s
1. create the disk (ebs) in our cloud provider

2. disk should be in the same az (availability zone) to mount the ebs volume

3. install the (ebs) csi drivers
kubectl apply -k "github.com/kubernetes-sigs/aws-ebs-csi-driver/deploy/kubernetes/overlays/stable/?ref=release-1.59"

4. EC2 nodes should have the IAM role access to mount the disks as ebs volumes
# We should have the ebs id to mount